result.execSummary:
The defendant Raul Jaimes-Vences was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Battery [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse Assessments], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(1).
  • Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse Assessments], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Raul Jaimes-Vences in court with attorney Olya Petukhova.  Porchia Sharese Lewand appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Sworn as interpreter: Daniel Lopez. State complied with victim notification. Sentencing Proceeded. Statements by parties, Mary L., and defendant.

AS TO COUNT 1
The court sentenced the defendant to 9 MONTHS in the House of Correction, consecutive, with credit for 4 days time served.  Court STAYED sentence and placed defendant on PROBATION for 24 MONTHS.

AS TO COUNT 2
The court sentenced the defendant to 3 MONTHS in the House of Correction, consecutive.  Court STAYED sentence and placed defendant on PROBATION for 24 MONTHS.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION
-Serve 30 days (on count 1) in the House of Correction as Condition Time, STAYED pending review.
-Batterers Intervention program.
-Parenting classes.
-AODA assessment, comply with recommended treatment.
-Treatment and/or counseling as determined by agent.
-No contact with victim BAR unless approved by the agent. Third party contact for purpose of time with the child/children remains.
-Obtain/maintain employment.
-No contact with firearms.
-Pay all MANDATORY court costs, fees, and surcharges including: DNA & DV surcharges during period of probation, failure to pay will result in a civil judgment. 
-Provide DNA Sample.
-Restitution set at ZERO.

*Court advised that under 48 USC Section 922(g)(9) the defendant is prohibited from possession of a firearm and/or ammunition after conviction of a crime of domestic violence.

Filed:

-Memorandum of Conditions of Probation
-Two letters on behalf of defendant
